        <td bgColor="black"><textarea cols="45" name="Message" rows="6" wrap="VIRTUAL">[quote]
Spells Used: Root, Enstill, Splurt, Bond of Death, Ignite Blood, Lich, Shield of Magi, Dead Man Floating, Feign Death, Thrall of Bones or other Charm, Dooming Darkness.

Strategy:
You must have big balls and be very talented at your class o do this solo. I have been very successful from 51 to 56 but it takes skill, timing and tenacity.

The zone to Howling Stones is found in the Overthere at the bottom of a canyon loc p800 n300. There is an elaborate quest for the keys to this dungeon that is posted on many spoiler sites so I will assume for the sake of this hunting guide that you have a key.

The Scorpicus outside of the zone will be KOS to you or will shortly after you spend time killing here. This dungeon effects faction negatively with Venril Sathir and Drusella Sathir. It is oddly positivie with Mayong Mistmoore.

Outside of zone buff up with your top skin and damage buffs. Cast DMF on yourself. If you have Jboots or Sow cast it but this is optional. Invis yourself.

When you zone into this dungeon you are in the middle of a square room with stairs on all four sides. You will zone into the exact center.

There will be two mobs who are in potential aggro range with you at zone in. Possible cobinations:

Bile Golem (Live)
Sepulcher Skeleton(Undead SK with Harm Touch)
Gnawer(Live)
Undead Oblation(Undead wimp caster)
Greater Plaguebone(Undead Warrior)

As soon as you log in FD immediately. 

The keys to success in this dungeon:

*Pathing in this room is set as follows. There are four pillars. One on each corner of the main room. There is a walkway around the pillars that is before each set of stairs. With DMF you can cross the main area faster than the mobs can do the walkway.

*As long as you go around one of the pillars the mobs will ALWAYS go the long way to get to you. That means by criss-crossing the room and passing a pillar you can always get enough lead on the mobs to cast a root spell.

Break #1

Once you zone in Feign immediately. Take your time and watch the two roamers. Put the key in your hand away in inventory.

Select an undead.

The mobs will move around the room in a set pattern. When both mobs are either 
a: Behind the pillars 
b: On opposite end of room from you

You can get up and they will not aggro till they move. As long as more than 1/4 of the room is between you and mob you will not get aggro. 

Stand up and charm the first undead. Have it fight the second mob. Cast dooming on the second to snare and bond of death. Go into Lich form and move to the opposite side of room to med. Now keep your new pet targeted. If charm breaks you need to root it. Other mobs will be snared so not as much of a danger.

Once you kill the first mob get out your timer.

The entire room. 2 Roamers and 8 Golems is on a 21 minute respawn exactly. After first roamer dead start watch. Wait 4 minutes and kill the second roamer/pet.

Break #2

The odds of single pulling the golems(all golems are paired in sets of 2) goes up per level:


51 10%
52 20%
53 30%
54 50%
55 60%
56 80%
57 100%

You can pull the golems on the stairs from the opposite side of the room standing on the walkway facing the Golems.

Pull the first golem using Bond of Death. As soon as spell is cast run to the right to the corner. This will cause the mob to take the long route. If one came root it. If two came root one run across the room and FD. If FD fails get up and do laps across room till it sticks. The unrooted mob will go back. Once it is back in its home it will not aggro again. Stand up and apply ignite blood and splurt and bond. You can also use any other not root breaking dot. *Kurl note: You can use dots with a DD, with the fubar pathing you can ALWAYS get away from the mob to recast root once you learn the pathing*

At 51 I could kill 4 spawns in 21 minutes. At 56 I do 6.

What you have to know about this room.

1. The East stairs sparkles they are fake.

2. The higher level roamer on the east stairs can aggro

3. The whole room is suspended over a mob filled pit.

4. If things go wrong jump off the edge into the pit. You get 14 seconds of fall time before another mob will aggro with DMF. During the fall gate.

5. No pet unless you have other melee and healers with you.

This room will take time patience and pratice. It is however the single best exp and spell collection spot I have found in all post 50 EverQuest. You will die some to learn. The keys respawn with you at bind point if you die. A druid makes a fantastic companion. One druid and I are able to do 11 spawns in 21 minutes.

If the East roamer aggros get out. Jump off and gate.

Timing Timing Timing. If you mistime the room spawn you will be in the middle of a Dot/Root scenario and a sepulcher will spawn and Harm Touch you. It sucks.

Make sure you have full health and damage shield up before respawn."

[/quote]</textarea><br>
        

        </td>
      </tr>

